    "In [29], the deterministic flow for N interacting particles is formulated by explicitly including the interaction term K:(2.11) dX N,i (t) dt = Vo[p N t](X N,i (t), t)+ 1 N j K(X N,i (t), X N,j (t)), i = 1, • • •, N, X N,i (t0) ∼ µ0,where V o = V -K * p N t is defined by subtracting the mean-field interaction from the velocity field V[ pt] in our definition (2.6).",
